</indent></indent><indent>3.	<indent>Click <bold>Apply</bold> or <bold>OK</bold> in the <bold>Edit Alert Icon</bold> dialog window. <<Ishmail> inserts the new alert icon before the selected icon in the <bold>Icon Pattern List</bold> of the <bold>Alert Icons</bold> window.


</indent></indent>§

[CARD] ishmail.iconWin.addPB.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Alert Icon - New Button
Click <bold>New</bold> to begin adding a new alert icon. <italic>Ishmail</italic> displays the <bold>Edit Alert Icon</bold> window. Then:


<indent>1.	<indent>In the <bold>Pattern</bold> field, enter a string pattern that would appear in the header field of an incoming message.


</indent></indent><indent>2.	<indent>In the <bold>Pixmap</bold> field, enter the name of the pixmap that should be invoked when the string pattern is encountered in a message header.


