[CARD] ishmail.sendWin.optAddSigTB.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Append Signature Before Delivery
Toggle the <bold>Append signature before delivery</bold> button to append a custom signature to the outgoing message before delivery. The actual signature is specified in <fixed>$HOME/.signature</fixed> or in your <italic>Ishmail</italic> custom resource file.


<indent><indentright><bold><x-color><param>Green</param>TIP:</x-color></bold><indent>  To specify a custom signature in your <italic>Ishmail</italic> resource file, select the <bold>Preferences</bold> option of the Main Window <bold>Options</bold> pull-down menu. In the <bold><italic>Signature</italic></bold> field, enter the name of the file containing your custom signature.


</indent></indent></indentright><indent><indentright><bold><x-color><param>Blue</param>NOTE:</x-color></bold><indent>  If your <italic>.signature</italic> file is owned by you, is <italic>not</italic> writable by others, and is executable it will be treated as an executable program. <italic>Ishmail</italic> will run the file using your login shell, and capture its standard output as your signature.


</indent></indent></indentright>See the <bold>Signature Preferences</bold> dialog for information about signature files. You may have different signatures for internal mail versus external mail. You may also have plain text and enriched text versions of the internal and external signatures.


§

[CARD] ishmail.prefWin.win.HLP
[TITLE] Application Preferences
Choose the <bold>Application ...</bold> option from the <bold>Main</bold> window <bold>Options</bold> menu to customize a number of parameters and variables in your <italic>Ishmail</italic> environment, including mail directory and file locations, print command, Web browser command, and Alert bell volume.


The preferences that you can set with this option apply to the <italic>Ishmail</italic> program in general or to the <bold><italic>Main</italic></bold> window. There are several other options for setting preferences specific to the <bold><italic>Reading</italic></bold> window, the <bold><italic>Composition</italic></bold> window, etc.


<indent><indentright><bold><x-color><param>Blue</param>NOTE:</x-color></bold><indent>  The decision of which parameter or variable to place into which preference window was made in a way that seemed logical to the developers of <italic>Ishmail</italic>. You may not find a preference in the window you expect. If so, keep looking. You will find it eventually.


</indent></indent></indentright>More explicit help is available for each of the parameters that can be customized. Use the <bold>Help on Context</bold> function. Select <bold>On Context</bold> from the <bold>Help</bold> pull-down menu, then move the cursor over the item of interest and click the mouse.


