</indent></indent><indent>3.	<indent>Place the pointer in the <bold>Folder name</bold> text field and enter the name of the folder that should be used when the string pattern is encountered in a message header.


<indent><indentright><bold><x-color><param>Blue</param>NOTE:</x-color></bold><indent>  Folder names can be fully qualified path names or relative path names. Relative path names are resolved starting from your <fixed>$HOME</fixed> directory. Relative path names starting with a <fixed>+</fixed> or an <fixed>=</fixed> are resolved starting from your <bold><italic>Folder Directory</italic></bold>, which is typically <fixed>$HOME/Mail</fixed>.


</indent></indent></indentright></indent></indent><indent>4.	<indent>Click <bold>OK</bold> or <bold>Apply</bold> in the <bold><italic>Edit Automatic Mail Filing Rule</italic></bold> dialog window. 


</indent></indent>§

[CARD] ishmail.autoFileWinEntryWin.valueForm.ctx.HLP
