[CARD] ishmail.autoFileWin.viewDA.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Automatic Mail Filing Patterns List
This is a list of folder names and associated search patterns. You specify a string pattern for each folder name defined. When mail arrives <italic>Ishmail</italic> scans the headers for a match with the patterns. When a match is detected the mail message is saved to the associated mail folder, if <italic>Ishmail</italic> is configured for automatic mail filing.


You can insert a new pattern and command in front of existing ones, add to the end of the list, or delete one or more patterns and commands by pressing <bold>Insert</bold>, <bold>Edit</bold>, or <bold>Delete</bold> respectively.


§

[CARD] ishmail.autoFileWin.win.HLP
[TITLE] Automatic Mail Filing Window
The <bold><italic>Automatic Filing ...</italic></bold> option is similar to the <bold><italic>Alerts ...</italic></bold> option in that it is triggered when certain incoming mail arrives, and it is similar to the <bold><italic>Saving ...</italic></bold> option in that it influences which folder is used when a message is saved. 


With this option you can cause incoming mail to be moved automatically from you <bold><italic>InBox</italic></bold> to a specific folder.


