[CARD] ishmail.optHeadPB.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Displayed Headers Option
Choose the <bold>Displayed Headers</bold> option to specify the headers to be displayed in the <bold>Reading</bold> window. 


When you click <bold>Displayed Headers</bold>, <italic>Ishmail</italic> opens the <bold>Edit Displayed Headers</bold> window. Use the <bold>Edit Displayed Headers</bold> window to specify which headers to display and which to ignore. For example, you can display the headers <bold><italic>date</italic></bold>, <bold><italic>to</italic></bold>, <bold><italic>from</italic></bold>, and <bold><italic>subject</italic></bold> but ignore the headers <bold><italic>content-length</italic></bold>, <bold><italic>content-type</italic></bold>, <bold><italic>references</italic></bold>. 


