[CARD] ishmail.alertWinEntryWin.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Edit Alert Command Window
Use the <bold>Edit Alert Commands</bold> window to create or change an alert command.


Use the <bold>Pattern</bold> field to specify the string pattern to appear in the header field of an incoming message. Each pattern must have an associated command.


The pattern is evaluated as a <italic>regular expression</italic>, as defined by the UNIX <fixed>ed</fixed> command.


§

[CARD] ishmail.iconWinEntryWin.win.HLP
[TITLE] Edit Alert Icon Window
<bold>Alert icons</bold> are pixmaps which display in place of the standard <italic>Ishmail</italic> mailbox icon when incoming mail arrives. 


Use the <bold>Edit Alert Icon</bold> window define the alert icons you want to add, insert, or change in the <bold>Icon Pattern List</bold> of the <bold>Alert Icons</bold> window.


§

[CARD] ishmail.aliasWinEntryWin.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Edit Alias Window
The <bold>Edit Alias</bold> window is opened when you click the <bold>New</bold> button, the <bold>Insert</bold> button, or the <bold>Edit</bold> button in the <bold>Alias</bold> window.


If you clicked <bold>New</bold> or <bold>Insert</bold>, this window will be empty. You can enter a new alias and associated address. When you click <bold>OK</bold> or <bold>Apply</bold> the new alias is added to the list in the <bold>Alias</bold> window. If you click <bold>OK</bold> the window closes. If you click <bold>Apply</bold> the window stays open so you can enter another new alias.


If you clicked <bold>Edit</bold>, this window will be filled in with the existing alias name and address you selected from the list in the <bold>Alias</bold> window.


§

[CARD] ishmail.autoFileWinEntryWin.win.HLP
[TITLE] Edit Automatic Mail Filing Pattern Window
<bold>Automatic Mail Filing Patterns</bold> are used to scan message headers when incoming mail arrives. Mail matching the patterns is automatically moved to the associated mail folder and removed from the <bold><italic>InBox</italic></bold>.


Use the <bold>Edit Automatic Mail Filing Rule</bold> window define the patterns you want to add, insert, or change in the <bold>Pattern List</bold> of the <bold>Automatic Mail Filing</bold> window.


§

[CARD] ishmail.buttonEditWin.win.HLP
[TITLE] Edit Button Window
This window lets you edit the label of, or set the position of, a single
button. You must use this window once for each button you wish to
modify. 


See the context help for the <Bold>Label</Bold> and
<Bold>Position</Bold> fields for more information.


§

[CARD] ishmail.buttonWin.win.HLP
[TITLE] Edit Custom Buttons Window
Use the <bold>Edit Custom Buttons</bold> window to specify buttons to be displayed in a window. Specifically, you can create buttons for menu functions to streamline your use of <italic>Ishmail</italic>. You can set up different custom buttons for the <bold>Main</bold>, <bold>Reading</bold>, and <bold>Composition</bold> windows.


In the default setup, a group of useful buttons is provided with each of these windows.


The <bold>Edit Custom Buttons</bold> window shows two lists of button names. The top list shows all possible functions which can be assigned to a button in this window. The bottom list shows all buttons which have been activated for this window.


<indent><indentright><bold><x-color><param>Blue</param>NOTE:</x-color></bold><indent>  When a button is added to the <bold>Selected</bold> list, it's name is removed from the <bold>Available</bold> list. When a button is removed from the <bold>Selected</bold> list, it's name reappears in the <bold>Available</bold> list.


</indent></indent></indentright>The names given to the buttons in the <bold>Available</bold> list consist of words or phrases, separated by slashes (/), corresponding to menu and option names. For example, to close the current folder you would choose the <bold>Current</bold> option from the <bold>Close</bold> sub-menu of the <bold>Folder</bold> menu. Thus, the Button name is <bold>Folder/Close/Current</bold>. 


These names uniquely specify each function, but are usually too long to be useful as the label on the button. Each button can be assigned a label, which is a short, descriptive name. There are default labels for each button. You can use anything you want for a label. Short labels are recommended since long labels result in wide buttons.


By default, all buttons are the same size. The size is wide enough to fit the longest label. So, creating a button with a long label will force all buttons to be that wide. You can toggle <fixed>Off</fixed> the <bold>Make all buttons the same size option</bold>, and buttons will be trimmed to fit the width of their labels.


<indent><indentright><bold><x-color><param>Blue</param>NOTE:</x-color></bold><indent>  All buttons in a column must be the same size, so a button with a long label will cause the buttons above it and below it to be wide.


</indent></indent></indentright>To create a button:


<indent>1.	<indent>Single-click on the name of a button in the <bold>Available buttons</bold> list. Note that with drag select or Ctrl-click you can highlight more than one name.


</indent></indent><indent>2.	<indent>Click the down-arrow button, which moves the highlighted name(s) to the <bold>Selected buttons</bold> list. Or, use the middle mouse button to drag the highlighted names and drop them into the <bold>Selected</bold> list.


</indent></indent><indent>3.	<indent>In the <bold>Button placement</bold> area, specify the display location for the buttons.


</indent></indent><indent>4.	<indent>In the <bold>Number of rows</bold> field, specify the number of rows to use in displaying the buttons. Or, in the <bold>Number of columns</bold> field, enter the number of columns to use in displaying the buttons. Note that only one of these fields is activated, depending on the button placement you have selected.


</indent></indent>You should edit the labels of the buttons you create, and select names which are meaningful to you. To edit a button label:


<indent>1.	<indent>Double-click on a name in the <bold>Selected</bold> list.


The <bold>Edit Button</bold> window is displayed.


</indent></indent><indent>2.	<indent>Enter a short, descriptive label into the <bold>Label</bold> field.


</indent></indent><indent>3.	<indent>In the <bold>Position</bold> field, enter a numerical value to specify the order in which the button should appear. A value of one specifies the leftmost, or topmost button.


</indent></indent><indent>4.	<indent>Click <bold>OK</bold> to apply your changes and close the <bold>Edit Button</bold> window.


</indent></indent>After creating buttons and editing labels, click <bold>OK</bold> to apply your changes and close the <bold>Edit Custom Buttons</bold> window.


To remove one or more buttons, highlight their names in the <bold>Selected</bold> list and click the up-arrow button (or drag and drop into the <bold>Available</bold> list).


You can also use "drag and drop" to reorder the buttons in the <bold>Selected</bold> list.


§

[CARD] ishmail.headerWin.win.HLP
[TITLE] Edit Displayed Headers Window
Mail messages frequently contain numerous headers, many of which you do not want to see. To make the header display box more useful, you can filter out all but the headers that are of interest to you, such as <bold><italic>From:</italic></bold>, <bold><italic>To:</italic></bold>, <bold><italic>Date:</italic></bold>, <bold><italic>Cc:</italic></bold>, and <bold><italic>Subject:</italic></bold>.


Use the <bold>Edit Displayed Headers</bold> window to specify the headers you want displayed in the headers display area of the <bold>Reading</bold> window. There are two lists of headers, the <bold>Ignore</bold> list and the <bold>Display</bold> list. You activate one list or the other. If you select the <bold>Display</bold> list, you will see ONLY the headers in that list. If you select the <bold>Ignore</bold> list, you will see all headers EXCEPT those in the list.


<indent><indentright><bold><x-color><param>Green</param>TIP:</x-color></bold><indent>  You can use "drag and drop" to move headers from one list to the other. Click on a header name, drag to the other list while pressing the middle button, and drop by releasing the middle button.


</indent></indent></indentright>§

[CARD] ishmail.fontWin.win.HLP
[TITLE] Edit Fonts Window
Use the <bold>Edit Fonts</bold> window to specify which fonts you want to use. You can set fonts for four different types of text:


<indent><bold><<></bold><indent>   The labels on push buttons and the items in menus.


</indent></indent><indent><bold><<></bold><indent>   Labels (titles) of items.


</indent></indent><indent><bold><<></bold><indent>   The text in the Reading Window and Composition Window.


</indent></indent><indent><bold><<></bold><indent>   The items in various lists.


