The <bold>File Name Filter</bold> text field is a search field. To search for a file in the current directory, type the file name (you can use wild card characters) and click the <bold>Filter</bold> button or press <fixed>Return</fixed> (or <fixed>Enter</fixed>). The names of files that match the search pattern are displayed in the <bold>Folders</bold> field.


The default filter is the <fixed>*</fixed> wild card.


