§

[CARD] ishmail.boolExpWin.win.HLP
[TITLE] Find Message Window (Complex)
Use the expanded <bold>Find Message</bold> window perform complex searches on combinations of mail message elements, including:


<indent><bold><<></bold><indent>   Sender


</indent></indent><indent><bold><<></bold><indent>   Recipient


</indent></indent><indent><bold><<></bold><indent>   Subject


</indent></indent><indent><bold><<></bold><indent>   Message headers, in general


</indent></indent><indent><bold><<></bold><indent>   Message body (message text)


</indent></indent><indent><bold><<></bold><indent>   Message, both headers and body


</indent></indent><indent><bold><<></bold><indent>   Status


</indent></indent><indent><bold><<></bold><indent>   Message Number


</indent></indent><indent><bold><<></bold><indent>   Line count


</indent></indent><indent><bold><<></bold><indent>   Byte count


</indent></indent>To construct a complex search:


<indent>1.	<indent>Click on a text field associated with one of the message elements.


</indent></indent><indent>2.	<indent>Enter a pattern for which to search.


<indent><indentright><bold><x-color><param>Blue</param>NOTE:</x-color></bold><indent>  Complex search strings are case-sensitive. UNIX wild card characters are legal. Syntax conforms to that of standard UNIX <italic>regular expressions</italic>.


</indent></indent></indentright><indent><indentright><bold><x-color><param>Blue</param>NOTE:</x-color></bold><indent>  For the Date, Number, Line Count, and Byte Count fields click the menu button to the left of the field to select a comparison function:


</indent></indent></indentright><indent><bold><<></bold><indent>   Less than


</indent></indent><indent><bold><<></bold><indent>   Less than of equal to


</indent></indent><indent><bold><<></bold><indent>   Equal to


</indent></indent><indent><bold><<></bold><indent>   Greater than or equal to


</indent></indent><indent><bold><<></bold><indent>   Greater than


</indent></indent><indent><bold><<></bold><indent>   Not equal to


</indent></indent>As you enter the pattern, the button to the left of the field becomes selectable.


</indent></indent><indent>3.	<indent>Click the button associated with the element (at the left side of the row).


When you click the button the pattern is added to the expression area at the bottom of the window.


</indent></indent><indent>4.	<indent>Use the <bold>AND</bold>, <bold>OR</bold>, and <bold>NOT</bold> buttons, at the top of the window, to combine multiple patterns into a logical expression.


</indent></indent><indent>5.	<indent>Click one of the <bold>Find Next</bold>, <bold>Find Prev</bold>, or <bold>Find All</bold> buttons to search forward, backward, or to find and select all messages matching the patterns.


</indent></indent><indent>6.	<indent>Click the <bold>Clear</bold> button to remove all patterns from the expression area.


<indent><indentright><bold><x-color><param>Green</param>TIP:</x-color></bold><indent>  You can use the <fixed>Delete</fixed> or <fixed>Backspace</fixed> keys to selectively delete patterns from the expression area. Position the cursor next to a pattern by clicking the left mouse button.


</indent></indent></indentright></indent></indent><indent>7.	<indent>Click the <bold>Done</bold> button when you are finished searching.


</indent></indent>§

[CARD] ishmail.msgFindWin.win.HLP
[TITLE] Find Message Window (Simple)
Use the <bold>Find Message</bold> window perform simple searches of messages in the current folder. 


A <italic>simple search</italic> means this:


<indent><bold><<></bold><indent>   The search is <italic>case insensitive</italic>. The string <fixed>abc</fixed> will match <fixed>abc</fixed>, <fixed>ABC</fixed>, or <fixed>aBc</fixed>.


</indent></indent><indent><bold><<></bold><indent>   No <italic>wild card</italic> characters are recognized.


</indent></indent>To do a simple search, enter a string into the <bold>Search String</bold> field and click the <bold>Find</bold> button. The string you entered is searched for in either the headers or the body of the message.


If you want your search to be sensitive to upper or lower case characters, you want to use wild card characters, or you want to search for more than one pattern at a time, click the <bold>Complex Search</bold> button.


See the help card in the expanded <bold>Find Message</bold> menu for more information.


§

[CARD] ishmail.boolExpWin.applyPB.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Find Next (Complex Search) Button
Click <bold>Find Next</bold> to apply the query you have built in the <bold>Query Display Area</bold>. The message list in the <bold>Main</bold> window will be positioned at the first message which meets the search criteria, and that message will be selected (highlighted). If no messages meet the criteria, no messages are selected and you will see "No Matches Found" in the message area at the bottom of this window.


The search proceeds <italic>forward</italic> (from the top of the list toward the bottom of the list) starting from the currently selected message.


The <bold>Complex Find Message</bold> window stays open. You can click <bold>Find Next</bold> again to search for the next matching message, or click <bold>Done</bold> to close this window.


§

[CARD] ishmail.msgFindWin.findPB.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Find Next Button
Click <bold>Find Next</bold> to search for messages that include information matching the search string you entered. <italic>Ishmail</italic> selects the first message that matches the query in the current folder.


The search proceeds <italic>forward</italic> (from the top of the list toward the bottom of the list) starting from the currently selected message.


If you click <bold>Find Next</bold> again, the next occurrence of the pattern is found.


The <bold>Find Message</bold> window stays open, so that you can easily repeat searching, until you click the <bold>Done</bold> button.


§

[CARD] ishmail.boolExpWin.findPrevPB.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Find Previous (Complex Search) Button
Click <bold>Find Previous</bold> to apply the query you have built in the <bold>Query Display Area</bold>. The message list in the <bold>Main</bold> window will be positioned at the first message which meets the search criteria, and that message will be selected (highlighted). If no messages meet the criteria, no messages are selected and you will see "No Matches Found" in the message area at the bottom of this window.


The search proceeds <italic>backward</italic> (from the bottom of the list toward the top of the list) starting from the currently selected message.


The <bold>Complex Find Message</bold> window stays open. You can click <bold>Find Previous</bold> again to search for the next matching message, or click <bold>Done</bold> to close this window.


§

[CARD] ishmail.msgFindWin.findPrevPB.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Find Previous Button
Click <bold>Find Previous</bold> to search for messages that include information matching the search string you entered. <italic>Ishmail</italic> selects the first message that matches the query in the current folder.


The search proceeds <italic>backward</italic> (from the bottom of the list toward the top of the list) starting from the currently selected message.


If you click <bold>Find Previous</bold> again, the next occurrence of the pattern is found.


The <bold>Find Message</bold> window stays open, so that you can easily repeat searching, until you click the <bold>Done</bold> button.


§

[CARD] ishmail.editFixedPB.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Fixed Option
Click <bold>Fixed</bold> to switch the selected text to a fixed font (that is, a mono-width, or non-proportional font).


When you apply the <bold>Fixed</bold> attribute, and you are displaying text in a fixed font already, you may not see much of a change. The default font <italic>Ishmail</italic> uses for text is a <italic>Courier</italic> font and the font used when displaying the <bold>Fixed</bold> attribute is called <italic>Fixed</italic>. Usually, these two fonts appear somewhat different even though both are fixed fonts. Even if the fonts appear the same to you the <bold>Fixed</bold> attribute is embedded in the text, and can be seen by the recipient, depending on the font specified for the <bold>Reading</bold> window.


<indent><indentright><bold><x-color><param>Blue</param>NOTE:</x-color></bold><indent>  <italic>Ishmail</italic> uses a fixed font by default in the <bold>Composition</bold> window because most other mail tools use a fixed font. If you use a proportional font when composing messages your text may not look very good when viewed by a recipient using a different mail tool. 


</indent></indent></indentright>§

[CARD] ishmail.folderSysPB.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Folder - Activate In-box Option
Choose <bold>Activate In-box</bold> to switch from the current active mail folder to the <bold><italic>In-box</italic></bold> mail folder. The contents of the active folder are shown in the <bold>Messages</bold> area.


§

[CARD] ishmail.folderActCB.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Folder - Activate Option
Choose <bold>Activate</bold> from the <bold>Folder</bold> menu to switch from the current active mail folder to the <bold><italic>In-box</italic></bold> or to the folder you have selected (highlighted) in the <bold>Open folders</bold> area.


§

[CARD] ishmail.folderActSelPB.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Folder - Activate Selected Option
Choose <bold>Activate Selected</bold> to move to the folder that you have highlighted in the <bold>Open folders</bold> area. The contents of the active folder are shown in the <bold>Messages</bold> area.


<indent><indentright><bold><x-color><param>Blue</param>NOTE:</x-color></bold><indent>  The <bold>Activate Selected</bold> option is usable only when you have highlighted a single folder in the <bold>Open folders</bold> area.


</indent></indent></indentright>§

[CARD] ishmail.folderCloseCB.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Folder - Close Option
Closes one or more mail folders. Selecting the <bold>Close</bold> option causes a cascading menu to be displayed from which you can choose one of three selection options:


<bold><italic><bold>Current</bold></italic></bold>

<indent>Closes the currently active folder, causing its icon to be removed from the <bold>Open Folders</bold> viewing area. The <bold>In-box</bold> then becomes the active folder and its contents are displayed in the <bold>Folder Contents</bold> viewing area. 


If any changes you have made to the current folder are outstanding, a confirmation dialog window asks if you wish to save the changes before closing the folder. 


</indent><bold><italic><bold>Selected</bold></italic></bold>

<indent>Closes one or more selected folders, causing their icons to be removed from the <bold>Open Folders</bold> viewing area. If a selected folder is currently active, the <bold>In-box</bold> then becomes the active folder by default, and its contents are displayed in the <bold>Folder Contents</bold> viewing area. 


If any changes you have made to the selected folder(s) are outstanding, a dialog window asks if you wish to save the changes before closing the folder.


You cannot close the <bold>In-box</bold> except by exiting from the program.


</indent><bold><italic><bold>All</bold></italic></bold>

<indent>Close all the folders in the <bold>Open Folders</bold> area.


</indent><indent><indentright><bold><x-color><param>Blue</param>NOTE:</x-color></bold><indent>  You can't close the <bold>In-Box</bold> folder. This folder always remains open.


</indent></indent></indentright>§

[CARD] ishmail.folderNewPB.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Folder - Create New Folder Option
Choose <bold>New</bold> to create a new mail folder.


