[CARD] ishmail.common.helpMenu.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Help Menu
Use the <bold>Help</bold> menu to determine the type of Help information to display:


<bold><italic><bold>On Context</bold></italic></bold>

<indent>Explains window components such as menus, labels, fields, and buttons. When you select <bold>On Context</bold>, the pointer turns into a question mark. To display the Help message for a specific component, place the question mark on the component and click.


<indent><indentright><bold><x-color><param>Green</param>TIP:</x-color></bold><indent>  To see <bold>On Context</bold> help for a menu option, first select the menu then click on the dotted line at the top of the menu. This "tears off" the menu so it stays displayed. Now, go to the <bold>Help</bold> menu, select <bold>On Context</bold>, bring the mouse cursor back to the torn off menu, and click on the option for which you want to see the Help message.


</indent></indent></indentright><indent><indentright><bold><x-color><param>Blue</param>NOTE:</x-color></bold><indent>  The <bold>On Context</bold> help is very sensitive to cursor position. If you don't position the cursor directly over a window component, you may just see the <bold>On Window</bold> help card. Also, in some cases you may see the <bold>On Context</bold> help card if you click on a field, but not when you click on the field's label.


</indent></indent></indentright></indent><bold><italic><bold>On Window</bold></italic></bold>

<indent>Describes the tasks you can perform from the window. There are two ways to see <bold>On Window</bold> help, depending on the window. If a window has a <bold>Help</bold> menu, choose <bold>On Window</bold> from the menu. If a window instead has a <bold>Help</bold> button, click the button.


</indent><bold><italic><bold>On Application</bold></italic></bold>

<indent>Explains <italic>Ishmail's</italic> purpose and basic capabilities. Introduces important concepts and terms.


</indent><bold><italic><bold>Index</bold></italic></bold>

<indent>Lists each of <italic>Ishmail's</italic> components for which you can get help.


</indent><bold><italic><bold>On Help</bold></italic></bold>

<indent>Describes the on-line Help system


</indent><bold><italic><bold>On Keys</bold></italic></bold>

<indent>Details <italic>Ishmail's</italic> keyboard shortcuts.


</indent><bold><italic><bold>On Version</bold></italic></bold>

<indent>Displays <italic>Ishmail's</italic> version number, copyright statement, and trademark and licensing information.


</indent><bold><italic><bold>User Guide</bold></italic></bold>

<indent>Your Web browser command is launched with the URL of the on-line version of the <italic><underline>Ishmail User's Guide</underline></italic>, which provides more detailed information than is available in the <bold>Help Cards</bold>.


</indent>
<bigger><bold><underline>Quick Help</underline></bold></bigger>


Along the bottom of each window there is a message area and a quick help area. The message area shows informational messages from <italic>Ishmail</italic>. The quick help area shows brief, helpful hints about an item which is currently under the mouse cursor.


<indent><indentright><bold><x-color><param>Green</param>TIP:</x-color></bold><indent>  You can turn off quick help if you want. To do so, use the <bold>Preference</bold> window from the main window <bold>Options</bold> menu. Turning off quick help can improve performance of the program when it is being used across a slow communications link.


</indent></indent></indentright>§

