[CARD] ishmail.app.HLP
[TITLE] Ishmail
[LOCATOR] 0.JlaEBGGWwA0YK
<italic>Ishmail</italic> is a versatile and user-friendly tool for reading, composing and organizing electronic mail. With <italic>Ishmail</italic>, you can:


<bold><italic>Work with varying file types</italic></bold>

<indent><italic>Ishmail</italic> supports standard ASCII messages, rich text, and the Multipurpose Internet Mail Extension (MIME), a standard for sending multi-media files via electronic mail.


MIME support is one of <italic>ishmail's</italic> most powerful features. When you compose a message you can use plain ASCII text or format the text with attributes such as different fonts and point sizes, and the text can be centered, right justified, or left justified. If you are reading a message containing MIME rich text you can see the formatting and you can also print the message to a PostScript printer. 


There are numerous other MIME data types including graphical and audio data. You can read and compose messages containing MIME <italic>attachments</italic>.


</indent><bold><italic>Customize your mail environment</italic></bold>

<indent>With <italic>Ishmail</italic>, you can specify and control many aspects of the user interface through dialog windows. You can control how folder and message contents are presented and sorted, you can define and modify shortcut buttons, and so on. See the <bold>Options</bold> pull-down menu for more details.


</indent><bold><italic>Display and store messages in multiple folders</italic></bold>

<indent>Incoming mail automatically appears in the <bold>In-box</bold> folder. You can transfer mail from the <bold>In-box</bold> to other folders, save messages to multiple folders, and work with multiple folders simultaneously.


<italic>Ishmail</italic> supports three types of folder formats, <italic>Unix mail</italic>-style (used by <fixed>mailx</fixed>, <fixed>elm</fixed>, etc.), <italic>mh</italic>-style (used by <fixed>mh</fixed>, <fixed>xmh</fixed>, etc.), and <italic>MMDF</italic>-style. These are the three most common mail folder formats used in <italic>Unix</italic> systems, so you should have no trouble sharing mail folders with other programs.


</indent><bold><italic>Easily manage mail messages</italic></bold>

<indent><italic>Ishmail</italic>'s user-friendly interface provides quick and easy ways to read, print, copy, delete, send and reply to mail messages.


You can also have incoming mail sorted by a criteria you define, and automatically filed to a specific folder. And, you can set up commands which are triggered by incoming mail. These commands can act upon the contents of the mail, for example: generate an automatic reply to a message.


</indent><bold><italic>Easily access on-line help</italic></bold>

<indent>QuickHelp messages at the bottom of each window remind how to use <italic>Ishmail</italic> features. <italic>Ishmail</italic> also provides <bold>Help</bold> buttons for access to information on using a window, and a <bold>Help</bold> menu with access to different types of information on <italic>Ishmail</italic> components.


</indent>§

