[CARD] ishmail.keys.HLP
[TITLE] Keyboard Shortcuts
<italic>Ishmail</italic> uses the standard Motif key bindings as well as some custom mappings.


Many commonly used functions have an associated shortcut key. The Control (<bold>Ctrl</bold>) key is used to activate shortcuts. If a function has a shortcut key, you will see its name to the right of the function name in a menu. For example, pull down the <bold>File</bold> menu. The Print and Exit functions have shortcut keys (<bold>Ctrl-P</bold> and <bold>Ctrl-E</bold>, respectively).


You can also start some features of this application using the <bold>Meta</bold> key in combination with a mnemonic defined by the underlined letter in a menu or option name.


<indent><indentright><bold><x-color><param>Blue</param>NOTE:</x-color></bold><indent>  On <italic>Sun</italic> keyboards, the <bold>Meta</bold> key is the key with the diamond symbol, to the right of the <bold>Alt</bold> key. On systems which don't have a <bold>Meta</bold> key, the <bold>Alt</bold> key provides this function.


</indent></indent></indentright>Once you have activated a menu with the <bold>Meta</bold> key, type the underlined letter in a menu option to select it. Or, use the cursor arrow keys to move the selection focus to an option, then press the <bold>Return</bold> (or <bold>Enter</bold>) key.


Another way to select the menu bar is to press the <bold>F10</bold> key (if your keyboard has one).


In the <bold>Message List</bold>, the cursor arrow keys can be used to move the outline box from message to message. Press the <bold>Space</bold> bar to select the message inside the outline box. Once a message is selected, shortcut keys can then be used (for example, <bold>Ctrl-R</bold> to read the message, <bold>Ctrl-D</bold> to delete it). When you are reading messages, <bold>Ctrl-Z</bold> advances to the next message and <bold>Ctrl-A</bold> moves back to the previous one.


Shortcut keys can also be used in combination. For example, there isn't a specific shortcut key for the <bold>Send/Close</bold> function, but there are shortcuts for <bold>Send</bold> (<bold>Ctrl-S</bold>) and <bold>Close</bold> (<bold>Ctrl-C</bold>). So, to send a message and close the <bold>Composition</bold> window, press and hold the <bold>Ctrl</bold> key while pressing <bold>S</bold>, then <bold>C</bold>.


To get <bold>On Context Help</bold> for a window item, position your pointer on the item and press <bold>Shift - F1</bold>, then the <bold>Return</bold> (or, <bold>Enter</bold>) key.



