If you have been composing a message, then you close the <bold>Composition</bold> window without first sending the message, the message will be saved to the file you specify in the <bold>Save interrupted messages to file</bold> field.


The default file name is: <fixed>$HOME/Mail/dead.letter</fixed>.


You can disable this function by setting the toggle button <fixed>Off</fixed>.


§

[CARD] ishmail.mailPrefWin.otherHeadText.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Mail Preferences - Specify Extra Mail Headers
You may want to add extra mail headers to your mail message, for example:


<indent><bold><<></bold><indent>   <bold>Reply-To:</bold>


</indent></indent><indent><bold><<></bold><indent>   <bold>Organization:</bold>


</indent></indent><indent><bold><<></bold><indent>   <bold>X-Face:</bold>


</indent></indent>Any mail headers you enter into this field will be included in every subsequent message you send.


<indent><indentright><bold><x-color><param>Blue</param>NOTE:</x-color></bold><indent>  <italic>Ishmail</italic> doesn't check the validity of information you specify here. You are responsible for using valid header names and spelling them correctly.


</indent></indent></indentright>§

[CARD] ishmail.mailPrefWin.sendmailTF.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Mail Preferences - Specify Mail Delivery Command
This is the name of the mail transport command <italic>Ishmail</italic> uses to send mail. The default is the <fixed>sendmail</fixed> command. You may want to use a different command. Or, the <fixed>sendmail</fixed> command may be in a different directory on your system, and you just need to change the path name.


<italic>Ishmail</italic> passes two parameters to the command, <fixed>-oi</fixed> and <fixed>-oem</fixed>. If the message is being sent in multiple pieces, the <fixed>-odi</fixed> parameter is added also.


After the parameters the recipients' addresses are added, each enclosed in single quote characters. This allows addresses to have embedded double quotes and blanks (spaces).


After the addresses, a <fixed><<</fixed> symbol is added followed by the path name of a temporary file which holds the complete message.


<indent><indentright><bold><x-color><param>Green</param>TIP:</x-color></bold><indent>  If you want to use a mail transport command which accepts different parameters than <fixed>sendmail</fixed>, you can put the name of a <italic>wrapper</italic> command here. For example, this can be the name of a shell script which converts the parameters to the format required before passing them on to the other command.


</indent></indent></indentright>§

[CARD] ishmail.mailPrefWin.splitTB.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Mail Preferences - Split Large MIME Messages
Click this button to cause large outgoing messages to be split into smaller parts, to be reassembled by the recipient's MIME mail reader. If the recipient of the message doesn't have the capability to reassemble messages automatically, your message will appear as two or more messages.


§

[CARD] ishmail.mailPrefWin.checkAddrTB.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Mail Preferences - Validate Addresses Before Using
Toggle this button <fixed>On</fixed> to cause <italic>Ishmail</italic> to use the <fixed>sendmail</fixed> command's address checking option to validate that the address(es) in your message are valid. This will prevent mail from bouncing, but it may take a long time to do the checking depending on the address and how you are connected to the Internet.


<indent><indentright><bold><x-color><param>Green</param>TIP:</x-color></bold><indent>  If you leave this option disabled, and a message you send bounces, use the <bold>Resend</bold> function to bounce it back again after you have determined the correct address. You do not need to re-compose the message.


</indent></indent></indentright><indent><indentright><bold><x-color><param>Red</param>WARNING:</x-color></bold><indent>  When validating an address such as <fixed>user@site.com</fixed>, the <italic>sendmail</italic> program may report that the address is valid as long as <fixed>site.com</fixed> is a valid domain, without verifying that <fixed>user</fixed> is, in fact, a valid address in that domain.


</indent></indent></indentright>§

[CARD] ishmail.optSigPB.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Mail Signatures Option
Choose the <bold>Signature ...</bold> option to customize how signatures are used in your messages.


