[CARD] ishmail.mainShell.folderForm.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Open Folders Area
The <Bold>Open folders</Bold> area displays your default
<Bold><Italic>In-box</Italic></Bold> mail folder and any additional mail
folders you open. When a mail folder is displayed in the <Bold>Open
folders</Bold> area, it is represented by a mailbox icon. 



<Underline><Bigger><Bold>In-box Mail Folder
</Bold></Bigger></Underline>


<Italic>Ishmail</Italic> automatically opens the
<Bold><Italic>In-box</Italic></Bold> mail folder when you start the
program. By default, the <Bold><Italic>In-box</Italic></Bold> folder is
always open and, initially, is the <Italic>active</Italic> mail folder.
Multiple mail folders can be open in the <Bold>Open folders</Bold> area,
but only one mail folder can be <Italic>active</Italic> at a time.


You can determine the status of your incoming mail by noting changes in
the <Bold><Italic>In-box</Italic></Bold> icon. 


<Indent><Bold><<></Bold><Indent>   An open door indicates that the
<Bold><Italic>In-box</Italic></Bold> mail folder is active. 


</Indent><Bold><<></Bold><Indent>   If new mail has arrived, or if there
is unread mail in the box from a previous session, the flag on the side
of the mailbox is up and envelopes appear inside. 


</Indent><Bold><<></Bold><Indent>   If there is no new or unread mail in
the folder, the flag is down and there are no envelopes inside the
mailbox.


</Indent></Indent> <Underline><Bigger><Bold>Other
Mailboxes</Bold></Bigger></Underline>


You can display additional mailboxes in the <Bold>Open folders</Bold> area
by choosing the <Bold>Open</Bold> option from the <Bold>Folder</Bold> menu
and selecting the additional mail folder(s) you wish to open.



<Underline><Bigger><Bold>Mail Folder
States</Bold></Bigger></Underline>


The types of actions you can perform on mail folders are determined by
functional states. Mail folders have three functional states:


<Indent><Bold><<></Bold><Indent>   <Italic>Open</Italic>


</Indent><Bold><<></Bold><Indent>   <Italic>Selected</Italic>


</Indent><Bold><<></Bold><Indent>   <Italic>Active</Italic>


</Indent></Indent> <Underline><Bold>Open State</Bold></Underline>

To view a mail folder in the <Bold>Open folders</Bold> area, that folder
must be open. You open a folder by selecting <Bold>Open</Bold> from
<Italic>Ishmail's</Italic> <Bold>Folder</Bold> menu. The <Bold>Selected
Folders</Bold> window appears. You can either type the name of the mail
folder(s) to open, or click <Bold>Show list</Bold> to reveal a list of
mail folders and directories. You can then select specific folders from
the <Bold>Folders</Bold> list. 



<Underline><Bold>Selected State</Bold></Underline>

To perform an action on a folder in the <Bold>Open folders</Bold> area,
you must first <Italic>select</Italic> the folder. 


You select a folder by clicking its mailbox icon. The selected folder is
then highlighted. You can perform various administrative actions on a
selected folder. 


You can select multiple folders either by either shift-clicking each
folder you want to select, or by placing the mouse pointer onto a folder
and "dragging" the mouse pointer across other folders you want to
select. The folders you choose by this <Italic>drag-select</Italic> method
must be contiguous.


To select noncontiguous folders, hold the Control key while clicking the
left mouse button on each folder you want to open.



<Underline><Bold>Active State</Bold></Underline>

To read the contents of a mail folder, that folder must be made
<Italic>active</Italic>. When a mail folder becomes
<Italic>active</Italic>, its mailbox icon is shown with its door open,
and its contents are displayed in the <Bold>Folder</Bold> contents area
for you to read. When you <Italic>activate</Italic> a folder, the
previously active folder becomes <Italic>inactive</Italic>, but remains
open in the <Bold>Open folders</Bold> area.


There are four ways to activate a folder.


<Indent>1.	<Indent>Click on a folder in the <Bold>Open folders</Bold> area
and choose the <Bold>Activate</Bold> option in the
<Bold>Folder</Bold> menu. 


</Indent>2.	<Indent>Place the mouse pointer on the mail folder you wish
to activate, press and hold the right mouse button, then select the
<Bold>Activate</Bold> option from the pop-up menu that appears.


</Indent>3.	<Indent>Select the <Bold>Open</Bold> option from the
<Bold>Folder</Bold> menu. The <Bold>Files</Bold> list window appears.
Click on a mail folder in the <Bold>Files</Bold> list window. 


</Indent>4.	<Indent>Double-click any <Italic>open</Italic> mail folder
currently displayed in the <Bold>Open folders</Bold> area. 


</Indent></Indent> <Underline><Bold>Closed State</Bold></Underline>

When you close a mail folder, it is removed from the <Bold>Open
folders</Bold> area. You can close a single folder or you can close
several folders as a group. There are two ways to close a single mail
folder.


To close a single mail folder:


<Indent>1.	<Indent>Select the folder by clicking its mailbox icon, then
choose <Bold>Close selected</Bold> from the <Bold>Folder</Bold> menu. 


</Indent>2.	<Indent>Place the mouse pointer on the mailbox icon of the
folder to close, then press and hold the right mouse button and select
<Bold>Close</Bold> from the pop-up menu that appears.


</Indent><IndentRight><X-Color><Param>blue</Param><Bold>NOTE:</Bold></X-Color><Indent>  If the folder you close is the
<Italic>active</Italic> folder, <Italic>Ishmail</Italic> automatically
activates the <Bold>In-box</Bold> folder.


</IndentRight></Indent></Indent>To close multiple folders:


<Indent>1.	<Indent>Select the folders to close, then choose the
<Bold>Close selected</Bold> option from the <Bold>Folder</Bold> menu. 


</Indent>2.	<Indent>Hold the Control key while clicking the left mouse
button on each folder to close (folders can be noncontiguous). Then
choose <Bold>Close selected</Bold> from the <Bold>Folder</Bold> menu.


</Indent>3.	<Indent>Choose <Bold>Select All</Bold> from the
<Bold>Folder</Bold> menu. Then select <Bold>Close selected</Bold> from
the <Bold>Folder</Bold> menu.


</Indent><IndentRight><X-Color><Param>blue</Param><Bold>NOTE:</Bold></X-Color><Indent>  If one of the folders you close is the
<Italic>active</Italic> folder, <Italic>Ishmail</Italic> automatically
activates the <Bold>In-box</Bold> folder.


</Indent></Indent> <Underline><Bigger><Bold>Folder Status

</Bold></Bigger></Underline>

A different icon is shown for the
<Bold><Italic>In-Box</Italic></Bold> folder, depending on whether you
have new mail. Optionally, different icons can also be shown for other
folders when they contain new mail. See the <Bold>Folder
Preferences</Bold> window (from the <Bold>Main</Bold> window
<Bold>Options</Bold> menu).


<Indent><X-Color><Param>green</Param>TIP:</X-Color> <Indent>This is most
useful if you are using the <Bold>Automatic Filing</Bold> feature. When
messages are automatically filed to a folder you can tell at a glance
from the folder icon.

</Indent>

</Indent> <Underline><Bigger><Bold>Folder Icon Size

</Bold></Bigger></Underline></IndentRight><Indent><Indent>

</Indent></Indent>You can change the icons which are shown for each
folder, using the <Bold>Folder Preferences</Bold> window. Choices are:


