[CARD] ishmail.prefWin.webBrowser.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Web Browser Command
<italic>Ishmail</italic> automatically recognizes addresses on the World Wide Web (known as URLs) which may be contained in mail messages, and highlights them in a different font or color. When you place the cursor on a URL and press the left mouse button while holding down the <fixed>Ctrl</fixed> key, the URL is sent to a Web browser command which will display the associated Web page.


This parameter lets you specify the Web browser command. Relative path names are resolved using your <fixed>$PATH</fixed> environment variable. The value of the URL is substituted for <fixed>%s</fixed>.


The default Web browser command is:


<fixed><bold>netscape -raise -remote `openURL(%s)' >>/dev/null 2>&1 || netscape -install `%s'</bold></fixed>


<indent><indentright><bold><x-color><param>Blue</param>NOTE:</x-color></bold><indent>  The default command uses the <italic>netscape</italic> browser. <italic>Ishmail</italic> will try to communicate with an already-running copy of <italic>netscape</italic>, if any, rather than starting a new command. This should greatly speed up access to URLs. 


</indent></indent></indentright><indent><indentright><bold><x-color><param>Blue</param>NOTE:</x-color></bold><indent>  Also the <bold>-install</bold> parameter is used with <italic>netscape</italic>. This will cause <italic>netscape</italic> to take control of the color map when running, resulting in use of truer colors in any graphics or pictures, though it temporarily causes other windows on your screen to look rather strange.


</indent></indent></indentright><indent><indentright><bold><x-color><param>Yellow</param>CAUTION:</x-color></bold><indent> You must exit and restart <italic>Ishmail</italic> for changes to take effect.


</indent></indent></indentright>§

[CARD] ishmail.readPrefWin.webTF.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Web Browser Command
Specify the command to be used for viewing a URL (<Italic>Universal
Resource Locator</Italic>, i.e. a World Wide Web address). URLs are
highlighted in the <Bold>Reading</Bold> window. Place the cursor over
the URL and press the CTRL key while clicking the mouse to cause the
external viewer to be launched.

 

<X-Color><Param>Green</Param>TIP:</X-Color><Indent> The default command
exploits a feature of the <Fixed><Bold>netscape</Bold></Fixed> browser
which lets you send it a new URL to view without launching another copy
of the program. Leaving a copy of
<Fixed><Bold>netscape</Bold></Fixed> running and using this feature
greatly reduces the delay between clicking the URL and seeing the Web
page.

</Indent>   

<X-Color><Param>Yellow</Param>CAUTION:</X-Color> <Indent>The default
command uses the <Bold>-install</Bold> flag with the
<Fixed><Bold>netscape</Bold></Fixed> browser. This causes
<Fixed><Bold>netscape</Bold></Fixed> to take over the color map when it
is running, so that it can best show true color images. A side effect is
the the colors of other programs look very strange while the
<Fixed><Bold>netscape</Bold></Fixed> window is in focus. Do not worry,
this is not a problem.

</Indent>
§

[CARD] ishmail.sendWin.sevFrame.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Weight Field
Use the <bold>Weight</bold> field to specify the importance of the comment which you are making about the product. The weight can be: <bold>Very High</bold>, <bold>High</bold>, <bold>Medium</bold>, <bold>Low</bold>, and <bold>Very Low</bold>. Click the button corresponding to the weight that most closely describes your comment.


Use <bold>Very High</bold> if the problem you are reporting results in lost or corrupted data.


Use <bold>High</bold> if the problem you are reporting prevents you from using one or more features of <italic>Ishmail</italic>.


Use <bold>Medium</bold> if the problem you are reporting can be circumvented.


Use <bold>Low</bold> if you are reporting a minor annoyance.


Use <bold>Very Low</bold> if you just feel like complaining but you don't expect an answer.


§

[CARD] ishmail.common.sash.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Window Sash Button
Click this button and drag up or down to change the relative sizes of
the top and bottom of the window.


For example, in the <bold>Main</bold> window this changes the relative sizes of the <bold>Open Folders</bold> area and the <bold>Message List</bold> area. In the <bold>Composition</bold> window this changes the relative sizes of the <bold>Headers</bold> area and the <bold>Message Text</bold> area.


§

[CARD] ishmail.readPrefWin.wrapTB.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Wrap Text at Right Margin in the Reading Window
If you select this option, <italic>Ishmail</italic> will reformat the text to best fit the number of columns in the Reading Window. 


If you turn off this option, <italic>Ishmail</italic> will place a horizontal scroll bar at the bottom of the text area if lines of text in the message area do not fit with window size.


<indent><indentright><bold><x-color><param>Blue</param>NOTE:</x-color></bold><indent>  If you make the window narrower than the width used by the sender of the message, formatting may not look good if you enable this option.


</indent></indent></indentright>

§

[CARD] ishmail.sendWin.optWrapTB.ctx.HLP
[TITLE] Wrap Text in the Composition Window
Toggle this button <fixed>On</fixed> to cause text to automatically break at the nearest word boundary and wrap to the next line when you type past the right margin. If not, a horizontal scroll bar will be added to the window if one or more lines in the message are longer than the window is wide. A change to this button does not remain in effect after you close the <bold>Composition</bold> window. See the <bold>Composition Window Preferences</bold> dialog if you want to change the default, which is <fixed>Off</fixed>.


